oc:kn_09261ea3 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When translating Python json module usage to Scala" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Prefer circe for JSON handling in Scala as it is the most popular and idiomatic library; use play-json as an alternative for Play framework projects." ;
    oc:hasRationale "circe provides type-safe, functional JSON serialization with automatic derivation, closely matching Python's ease of use while leveraging Scala's type system." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_478289cb a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting Python asyncio code to Scala" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For async/concurrent code, prefer cats-effect IO for FP-oriented projects or scala.concurrent.Future for simpler use cases." ;
    oc:hasRationale "cats-effect IO provides referential transparency and better composability for purely functional programs, while Future is sufficient for straightforward concurrent tasks." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_591372a2 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When translating Python re module usage to Scala" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
    oc:directiveContent """// Regex in Scala uses string .r method:
val pattern = \"\"\"\\d+\"\"\".r
pattern.findFirstIn(text) // Option[String]
pattern.findAllIn(text).toList // List[String]
pattern.replaceAllIn(text, "X") // String""" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Scala's built-in regex support via .r on strings is concise and integrates with pattern matching, differing from Python's re module API." .

oc:kn_6dfcddf4 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When translating Python open/with statements to Scala" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
    oc:directiveContent """// Scala file reading with resource safety:
import scala.util.Using
import scala.io.Source
Using(Source.fromFile("file.txt")) { source =>
  source.getLines().toList
}""" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Using provides safe resource management equivalent to Python's context managers, preventing resource leaks." .

oc:kn_92bfbb2b a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When translating Python @pytest.mark.parametrize to Scala" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
    oc:directiveContent """// Scala table-driven testing:
import org.scalatest.prop.TableDrivenPropertyChecks._
val examples = Table(("input", "expected"), (1, 2), (2, 4))
forAll(examples) { (input, expected) =>
  input * 2 shouldEqual expected
}""" ;
    oc:hasRationale "TableDrivenPropertyChecks is ScalaTest's equivalent to pytest's parametrize decorator." .

oc:kn_94397d8a a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning Python-to-Scala library migration" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not attempt to find a single Scala library that maps 1:1 to every Python standard library module; Scala's ecosystem is fragmented across multiple specialized libraries." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Python's batteries-included standard library contrasts with Scala's approach of using multiple focused libraries (circe for JSON, sttp for HTTP, pureconfig for config, etc.)." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_e0ad16da a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When translating Python json.dumps/json.loads to Scala" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
    oc:directiveContent """// Scala JSON with circe:
import io.circe._, io.circe.generic.auto._, io.circe.syntax._, io.circe.parser._
case class Person(name: String, age: Int)
val jsonStr: String = person.asJson.noSpaces
val parsed: Either[Error, Person] = decode[Person](jsonStr)""" ;
    oc:hasRationale "This is the standard circe pattern for serialization/deserialization that maps to Python's json module." .

oc:kn_e25d0d6c a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting Python datetime or os/pathlib code to Scala" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Scala relies on Java platform libraries for date/time (java.time) and file I/O (java.nio.file) rather than native Scala equivalents." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Scala interoperates seamlessly with Java standard library, and java.time/java.nio.file are the correct, well-maintained equivalents to Python's datetime and pathlib." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e767d19d a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When translating Python requests, logging, or argparse to Scala" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For Scala HTTP clients, use sttp; for logging, use scala-logging with logback; for CLI parsing, use scopt (OOP style) or decline (FP style)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These libraries are the most widely adopted and idiomatic choices in the Scala ecosystem for each respective domain." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

